{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491206","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491206"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:37:38+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:37:38+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"867"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/867"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.4,0.15,0.02,0.09,0.34]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"867"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84687"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/867"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"867"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68974"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"3"},{"type":"tags","id":"20"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"560"},{"type":"tags","id":"1213"},{"type":"tags","id":"4955"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11629"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5283"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6758"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13812"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34974"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42169"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"84687","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/84687"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 66-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a painless lump on the dorsum of her left hand. The lesion has been present for 20 years without change in appearance. She reports new symptoms of morning stiffness and swelling in both hands over recent months. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. There is a soft, mobile, well-defined subcutaneous mass on the dorsum of her left hand that is non-tender to palpation (Image). There is synovitis of the metacarpophalangeal joints bilaterally.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis for the hand mass?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Ganglion","Rheumatoid nodule","Gouty tophus","Epidermoid cyst","Lipoma"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with a long-standing soft tissue mass characteristic of a \u003Cstrong\u003Elipoma\u003C/strong\u003E. While lipomas most commonly occur on the trunk, they can develop anywhere adipose tissue is present. The key features supporting this diagnosis are the soft, mobile, well-defined nature of the mass and its stability over 20 years.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGanglions\u003C/strong\u003E are fluid-filled cysts that arise from joint capsules or tendon sheaths. They typically occur at the dorsal wrist, are firm rather than soft, and may fluctuate in size over time. They are often more tense to palpation than lipomas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERheumatoid nodules\u003C/strong\u003E develop in about 20% of patients with rheumatoid arthritis, usually after the onset of joint disease. While this patient\u0027s morning stiffness and synovitis suggest early rheumatoid arthritis, the 20-year history of the mass predates these symptoms, making a rheumatoid nodule unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGouty tophi\u003C/strong\u003E are firm, chalky deposits of urate crystals that develop in chronic gout. They typically appear years after the onset of gout attacks, are often multiple, and commonly affect the ears, elbows, and small joints of the hands. The absence of a gout history makes this diagnosis unlikely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpidermoid cysts\u003C/strong\u003E are dermal cysts containing keratin debris. They are typically more superficial than lipomas, have a visible central punctum, and are firm rather than soft. They can become inflamed or infected, unlike this patient\u0027s stable, asymptomatic mass.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lipomas, although commonly occurring on the trunk, can occur anywhere in the body where there is fatty tissue.","Lipomas are characteristically soft, mobile, well-defined subcutaneous masses that remain stable in size over many years.","Morning stiffness and bilateral hand swelling are characteristic features of rheumatoid arthritis, but rheumatoid nodules typically develop later in the disease course."],"references":["Yavari M, Afshar A, Shahraki SS, et al. Management of Symptomatic Lipoma of the Hand: A Case Series and Review of Literature. Arch Bone Jt Surg. 2022; 10: 530-35. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35928905/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68974"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"867"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"16857"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"16857","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/16857"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f78e2714-810f-4ef3-ae19-8c532e1242a7.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f78e2714-810f-4ef3-ae19-8c532e1242a7.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68974","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/68974"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-10T11:28:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-15T13:34:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"i